gtr:otherNames>Matthew</gtr:otherNames><gtr:surname>Kisby</gtr:surname><gtr:orcidId>0000-0001-9725-9737</gtr:orcidId><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FG010404%2F1"><gtr:id>6014084F-4F86-4A59-B5DD-7575B26D9157</gtr:id><gtr:title>New Labour and Citizenship Education</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/G010404/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This ESRC Post-Doctoral Fellowship will build on and develop the Fellow's PhD research on 'New Labour and Citizenship Education' by:&lt;/p>

&lt;p>a) Analysing how the concerns held by key individuals and groups about civic disengagement in Britain influenced the introduction of citizenship lessons in secondary schools in England in August 2002;&lt;/p>

&lt;p>b) Undertaking comparative research by examining how both the citizenship education policy in England and devolution are impacting on the development of citizenship education initiatives in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland. This will include conducting interviews in Westminster and Whitehall with former Cabinet colleagues of David Blunkett, the former Secretary of State for Education and Employment, Labour backbenchers and civil servants working in the then DFEE, and with policy-makers in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland; and&lt;/p>

&lt;p>c) Examining New Labour's broad approach to citizenship beyond citizenship education through analysing various policy interventions designed to promote community participation by UK citizens, including: constitutional reform, immigration and asylum and citizenship ceremonies and tests. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>This will enable the development of a detailed analysis of and explanation for the development of citizenship lessons across the UK and a comprehensive analysis of the concept of citizenship underpinning the development of New Labour policy more broadly.&lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2009-09-30</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2008-10-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>66673</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>AC6B57D1-681F-4B9E-B003-9F84CB0A23D2</gtr:id><gtr:title>The Labour Party and Citizenship Education: Policy Networks and the Introduction of Citizenship Lessons in Schools</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/d45d6744ecd4aa8286aa29e937513268"><gtr:id>d45d6744ecd4aa8286aa29e937513268</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Kisby Ben</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>9780719086229</gtr:isbn><gtr:outcomeId>i_31547229483b8fd8d4</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>0A54177D-E7DA-424C-9A7B-07EBDE5FA9A0</gtr:id><gtr:title>REVITALISING POLITICS: THE ROLE OF CITIZENSHIP EDUCATION</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Representation</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/8eaed3a4b0a72590703b1038430d969f"><gtr:id>8eaed3a4b0a72590703b1038430d969f